Astrea of the Stars 15-Aug-21 04:36 PM
Drake was in medbay— wait, he's not even the main host of this season. And this is the medical center, not the medbay! It's... fine, all things considered. There's about a dozen beds in this room - the beds themselves seemed like the ones you might find in an ordinary hospital, and didn't surprise you in the slightest. There's two other 'benches' that are simply somewhat comfortable slabs that someone could lie down on if they don't wish to get into a bed. There's no equipment near the beds, funny enough - you're completely on your own if you get injured. Actually, the missing equipment is clearly visible - you can tell that there's supposed to be something near the beds, but there's just an empty void instead. Oh right, the rest of the room! It's pretty standard, though the room is white and bright, unlike many of the other rooms. It's rather clean, smelling a bit like it was cleaned recently, no matter how far into the game you are at the time of reading this. There's nothing really fundamentally wrong with it... ...there is are some 'supply shelves' in the back of this place. It's behind glass doors that you can easily open, but there's not a whole lot in them - you get the feeling that many of the materials had been taken out. What's left is pretty basic - bandaids, medicines for coughs, colds, and other minor illnesses, some basic pain relievers that aren't that strong, and... poisons. Tons of them. All labeled neatly and all having detailed information on them explaining exactly how they worked. This is just poison central, isn't it?
